Installing MySQL on linux
Download the repo files(on host server) and save them in some(example tmp file)file.
Move those repo files to roles/install-mysql/files(create this dir)
And in install-mysql/tasks/main.yml 
1.copy those repo files to /etc/yum.repo.d/(some file).repo(for the remote server)
2.install mysql-community-server
3.start the service (mysql)

